If I come here and post that cars run on tooth paste and shaving cream either they damn well should or I should expect to be flamed regardless of how long I've been a mechanic.<br>
<br>
Your friend doesn't know as much as he thinks he does including how much his own spells are nerfed by in pvp.<br>
<br>
The only melee dmg that is extreme enough to even take a look at is that done by various discs.  If any of these are overpowered then its grounds for looking at these discs and not every melee attack at every lvl.<br>
<br>
Its also possible that certain hybrids are overpowered not because of their uber melee dmg but because of the combination of spells and skills available to them.  If you think that is grounds for discussion fine.<br>
<br>
Its also possible that the performance of melees in uber gear should be looked at.  However even if uber melee performance is way overpowered this is NOT a reason to nerf all melees nor is it a reason to buff up every naked caster pk who dings quading by increasing their spell dmg across the board.<br>
<br>
Casters feel free to keep posting exaggerated, poorly thought out, and pure and simple stupid solutions to balancing pvp...<br>
<br>
All real solutions must take into acount ALL effects and the real result for all parties.<br>
