<br>
All these paper arguements about a fully buffed, DS potioned FM necro against a level 60 that with 9 golem wands and full ToV gear are not very productive.  Banshee aura does 11 damage at level 44.  It's duration is so short as to be almost useless and I'd be even less inclined to PAY for a DS.  The fact is that you have to sit around getting hit on for the DS to pay for itself, which means dying, or wasting a damage skin/harmshield.  Unless I am fighting ONE particular low damage per hit melee, why would I bother with all that fufera?  If I was on a blue server duelling a rogue, sure.<br>
<br>
People don't spend 400pp in expendables before every fight - it's hard enough keeping buffs up that are important and &quot;free.&quot;  Similarly, noone actually uses necro debuff lines or nonsense like that.  That screams pve to me, people talking about theoretical uses for highly resistable spells that are a waste of time and mana in pvp.<br>
<br>
I don't feel I'm &quot;weak&quot; as a Nec on SZ, just more vulnerable than some people expect.  I can't use 15 of my wonderful spells every fight because I can only mem 8 in the first place, and tons of them don't land on anyone worth talking about anyway.  But any old even con who fears my pet and starts wailing on me puts me in an awkward position.  People go on and on about shadowstep, but it isn't something to bet your life on.  <br>
<br>
Also, do to things like casting on the run and pet kiting it's usually helpful to use an exterior camera, but assuming equal jboots or sow potions, this means a lower speed than a strafing melee.<br>
<br>
A_caster_00 says &quot;OMG Casters are so useless, damage nerf old spells, new gear, OMFG&quot;<br>
<br>
A_melee_00 says &quot;OMG Melees are so useless, range bug, lev, gear requirements&quot;<br>
<br>
blah blah<br>
